com.amplifyframework.core.model.annotations

Annotation Type ModelConfig


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface ModelConfig
    ModelConfig annotates any Model with applicable configuration information. The RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME annotation is added to retain ModelConfig at runtime for the reflection capabilities to work in order to check if this annotation is present for a field of a Model. ElementType.TYPE annotation is added to indicate ModelConfig annotation can be used only on types (class, interface, enum).
